-- Philippine Equity Movers: Atlas, Benguet, Philex Mining
-- B y   N o r m a n   P .   A q u i n o
-- 2012-06-08T07:50:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/atlas-consolidated-philippine-long-philippine-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Manila.  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  fell 0.6 percent to
4,994.07. The gauge declined 1.4 percent this week, its first
drop in three weeks.  Miners:  Benguet Corp. (BC)  class-A shares (BC PM) lost 5.7
percent to 21.65 pesos, the lowest close since Oct. 4. It led a
decline among Philippine metal producers as gold headed for a
weekly drop.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)   declined 1 percent to
23.70 pesos, the sharpest loss in four days.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development Corp. (AT)   fell
1.7 percent to 17.46 pesos, the lowest close since Feb. 14. The
miner said its copper unit had shipped $33.7 million worth of
the metal in May, lower than the $34.7 million shipped in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Norman P. Aquino in  Manila  at 
